{
  "texts": [
    "It will be challenging for non-classical biomarkers and GMAI approaches to meet explainability and transparency requirements in proposed regulations 14, 47.",
    "First generation cancer drug-companion apps provide simple digital support to patients undergoing cancer treatment to enhance patient understanding and adherence.",
    "They have simple diary, tracking and communications functions 53, 54, 70.",
    "Some of these apps use remote monitoring for dose adaptation to side effects, but, due to the increased HCP workload they create, and due to their lack of reimbursement, they have thus far only been used in clinical trials [71] [72] [73].",
    "These apps, depending on their precise purpose, are non-medical device apps (US and EU), medical device apps for which there is a regulatory non-enforcement approach (US) [37] [38] [39] or low risk class medical device apps (EU) 44, 46."
  ]
}